commentTextItems.html: fuller ball outside the off stump. He looks to go over long off. Gets an outside edge that Bonner runs back and takes. It's 3-0 for West Indies in the series

commentPostTextItems.html: That's it from all of us here. Thanks for joining us for the series. This is Thilak Ram signing off on behalf of Ranjith, take care and good night

Pooran, West Indies captain: Very pleased. First time being a captain and win the series 3-0. Netherlands played wonderfully as well. I am very happy for the guys as they took the opportunity and performed well. This is a game of cricket and everything can't go your way. Today Netherlands experienced a hard day. Am surprised with the crowd in Amsterdam. They came to watch every game.

Seelaar, Netherlands captain: We have competed in patches. We could've beaten West Indies. Very, very close games. This was a game today that we could've won with some experience. Very disappointed with the result today as we felt we deserved 10 points. We pulled it back nicely to keep them down to 308. We kind of lost it in the 35-40 overs as we weren't wanting to chase 100 and chase 80. Didn't happen.

Akeal Hosein is the player of the series: Yeah, pretty pleased with the effort on a batting-friendly wicket. First of all, kudos to Nicky P [Pooran] for the changes he made. Whatever the team requires, I am ready to put my hand up for that

Kyle Mayers is the player of the match: It was a good feeling. I got an opportunity to open the batting and it happened [the century]. It was a good experience and the wickets are good for batting. I want to make [opening] a permanent fixture. Let's see how it goes.

Both the teams stayed close in comparison till 37th over. The 38th over was a maiden in the Netherlands innings and it was also the time that Mayers reached his ton and unleashed an assault. Both the teams were poor in the final 10 overs. They lacked a finisher who could've stepped up a gear

West Indies win the series 3-0 and get the 30-points they could from this series. They move to the fourth spot in the table as Afghanistan won earlier today and they have a better NRR than West Indies
